<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Guillotine</h1>			<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
				<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>				<div id="contentSub"></div>
								<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">This article is about the device used to carry out executions by <a href="/wiki/Decapitation" title="Decapitation">beheading</a>. For the paper slicing tool, see <a href="/wiki/Paper_cutter" title="Paper cutter">Paper cutter</a>. For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Guillotine_(disambiguation)" class="mw-disambig" title="Guillotine (disambiguation)">Guillotine (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
